title.narrative: STRENGHTENED ENABLING ENVIRONMENT FOR RMNCAH

description.narrative: The health system has a strengthened enabling environment for RMNCAH., which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health And Emergencies, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Effective coverage of high-impact reproductive, maternal, neonatal, child and adolescent health (RMNCAH) interventions

title.narrative: The health system has a strengthened enabling environment for RMNCAH.

description.narrative: Significant;achievements were made despite the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic to strengthen the enabling environment for RMNCAH.;Health sector coordination through the;SWAp;mechanism continued with significant contributions from UNICEF and partners to;several;strategic documents;to guide the continuity and improvement of RMNCAH in the context of the broader health system and the pandemic response.;The capacity for;evidence based;planning;at district and health facility levels;was strengthened with increased ownership by the government;to;implement bottleneck analyses to guide priority setting.,;Contributions were made to evidence generation,;through embedded implementation research;into several programs,;and the preparations for the Tanzania Demographic and Health Survey.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:21/12/2021
